rs%20and%20consumers%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20lawsuit%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20Boats%20Group%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20on%20Monday%20from%20Business%20Insider.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F9-big-private-equity-firms-betting-on-e-commerce-2021-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPermira%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20global%20private%20equity%20firm%20that%20owns%20Boats%20Group%2C%20declined%20to%20comment.%20(Permira%20is%20not%20named%20as%20a%20defendant%20in%20the%20lawsuit).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%2C%20filed%20by%20Brill%20Maritime%20Inc.%2C%20which%20does%20business%20as%20Export%20Yacht%20Sales%2C%20seeks%20to%20%26quot%3Brestore%20competitive%20conditions%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20boat%20market%20and%20recover%20damages%20for%20any%20US%20individuals%20or%20businesses%20allegedly%20harmed%20as%20a%20result%20of%20Boat%20Group's%20%26quot%3Banticompetitive%20conduct.%26quot%3B%20The%20proposed%20class%20is%20estimated%20to%20be%20thousands%20of%20members%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20says%20that%20Boats%20Group%20publicly%20claims%20to%20control%20about%2075%25%20of%20the%20global%20market%20for%20online%20marine%20vessel%20listing%20and%20marketing%20services%20and%20that%20its%20share%20of%20the%20US%20market%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20similarly%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company's%20website%20says%20its%20platforms%20attract%20more%20than%2065%20million%20annual%20visitors%2C%20%26quot%3Bgiving%20sellers%20unmatched%20exposure%20to%20serious%20boat%20buyers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoats%20Group's%20subscription%20agreements%20with%20sellers%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bcontain%20exclusive%20dealing%20provisions%20that%20either%20prohibit%20or%20strongly%20discourage%20sellers%2C%20particularly%20brokers%20and%20dealers%2C%20from%20listing%20their%20inventory%20on%20competing%20platforms.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThrough%20subscriptions%2C%20boat%20sellers%20pay%20Boats%20Group%20to%20have%20their%20vessel%20inventory%20listed%20and%20marketed%20to%20a%20large%20swath%20of%20prospective%20buyers%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExport%20Yacht%20Sales%20says%20in%20the%20lawsuit%20that%20it%20purchases%20these%20subscriptions%20with%20Boats%20Group%20and%20that%20it%20has%20been%20forced%20to%20pay%20%26quot%3Bsupracompetitive%20prices%20for%20essential%20marketing%20services%2C%20with%20effectively%20zero%20viable%20alternatives%20available.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Miami%20brokerage%20says%20in%20the%20lawsuit%20that%20its%20combined%20monthly%20cost%20of%20listing%20on%20Boat%20Trader%20and%20YachtWorld%20skyrocketed%20by%20more%20than%20400%25%20between%202014%20and%202024%2C%20jumping%20from%20%241%2C004%20to%20%245%2C128.%20The%20plaintiff%20was%20charged%20%242%2C900%20a%20month%20by%20Boat%20Trader%20alone%20in%202025%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBoats%20Group's%20exclusionary%20behavior%20has%20suppressed%20competition%2C%20harmed%20sellers%20and%20brokerages%2C%20and%20distorted%20the%20structure%20and%20dynamics%20of%20the%20online%20boat%20sales%20marketplace%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20lawsuit%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20says%2C%20consumers%20are%20met%20with%20fewer%20options%20and%20higher%20prices%20for%20their%20boating%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20dominance%20has%20enabled%20Boats%20Group's%20predatory%20conduct%20to%20persist%20over%20time%2C%20allowing%20it%20to%20impose%20supracompetitive%20prices%20for%20subscription-based%20listing%20and%20marketing%20services%20without%20losing%20significant%20business%20to%20rivals%2C%20restrict%20sellers'%20ability%20to%20switch%20to%20alternative%20services%2C%20and%20foreclose%20entry%20and%20expansion%20by%20rival%20platforms%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20lawsuit%20alleges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAttorneys%20for%20Export%20Yacht%20Sales%20told%20Busin