-coasts-2020-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eliving%20around%20the%20East%20Coast%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20fact%2C%20each%20of%20our%20three%20kids%20was%20born%20in%20a%20different%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20fall%20of%202020%2C%20my%20wife%20was%20looking%20to%20relocate%20to%20someplace%20where%20she%20could%20practice%20medicine%20in%20an%20indigenous%20community.%20Her%20primary%20targets%20were%20Alaska%2C%20the%20%26quot%3BFour%20Corners%26quot%3B%20(or%20where%20the%20states%20Arizona%2C%20Colorado%2C%20New%20Mexico%2C%20and%20Utah%20intersect)%2C%20and%20Hawaii%2C%20all%20of%20which%20desperately%20needed%20doctors%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20during%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20when%20she%20announced%20that%20she'd%20actually%20landed%20an%20offer%20to%20work%20at%20a%20hospital%20in%20Hawaii%2C%20I%20had%20mixed%20feelings.%20On%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20it%20had%20a%20special%20place%20in%20our%20hearts%20as%20we'd%20gotten%20married%20there%20in%202008.%20On%20the%20other%2C%20we%20had%20just%20purchased%20a%20nice%20four-bedroom%20house%20with%20an%20indoor%20pool%20in%20Albany%2C%20New%20York.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20wasn't%20just%20that%20I%20was%20having%20a%20hard%20time%20letting%20go%20of%20what%20I%20thought%20would%20be%20our%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-planned-to-rent-forever-then-i-bought-a-house-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eforever%20house%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20Things%20between%20us%20had%20already%20been%20rocky%20%E2%80%94%20and%20moving%20to%20paradise%20wasn't%20going%20to%20automatically%20fix%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20I%20listened%20to%20my%20gut%2C%20which%20told%20me%20to%20stay%20behind%20in%20New%20York%20and%20take%20some%20space%2C%20even%20though%20my%20freelance%20writing%20allowed%20me%20to%20work%20from%20anywhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221bec03c3-c1f1-4923-8c72-e62fb65dfb0c%5C%22%3EThey%20left%2C%20I%20cried%2C%20and%20I%20eventually%20left%20New%20York%20to%20join%20them%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Aloha%20sign%20in%20Hawaii%20with%20kids%20posing%20iwth%20it%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6888f84e85e81483682eda0c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAt%20first%2C%20it%20was%20tough%20seeing%20my%20family%20move%20to%20Hawaii%20without%20me.%3Cp%3EScott%20Tharler%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESeeing%20them%20go%20in%202021%20wasn't%20easy.%20I%20can%20still%20picture%20my%20son%20(who%20was%204%20years%20old%20at%20the%20time)%20waving%20his%20little%20hand%20goodbye%20from%20the%20airport%20security%20line.%20I%20cried%20for%20several%20hours%20that%20day%2C%20wondering%20whether%20I'd%20made%20a%20good%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20couple%20of%20months%20later%2C%20I%20flew%20out%20to%20visit%20them.%20After%20touring%20the%20island%20for%20a%20few%20days%2C%20I%20saw%20the%20gorgeous%20house%20they%20were%20renting%20in%20Honokaa%2C%20situated%20on%20a%201%2C000-foot%20cliff%20overlooking%20the%20ocean.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20proud%20of%20the%20life%20they'd%20set%20up%2C%20but%20sadly%2C%20I%20also%20felt%20like%20an%20outsider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20weeks%20after%20I%20returned%20east%20by%20myself%2C%20the%20five%20of%20us%20met%20in%20California%20for%20a%20family%20vacation%2C%20after%20which%20the%20kids%20and%20I%20flew%20to%20Albany%20for%20the%20summer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20July%2C%20the%20four%20of%20us%20jetted%20back%20to%20the%20island.%20This%20time%2C%20I%20stayed%20for%20the%20whole%20school%20year%20in%20the%20house's%20ohana%2C%20a%20separate%20living%20space%20over%20the%20garage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20many%20ways%2C%20this%20exemplifies%20the%20gray%20area%20in%20my%20relationship%20with%20my%20wife%20%E2%80%94%20amicable%20enough%20to%20be%20close%20but%20not%20%3Cem%3Etoo%3C%2Fem%3E%20close.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%