Why%20tomatoes%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%2C%20being%20the%20second-largest%20producer%20of%20tomatoes%20with%20about%2044%20million%20tons%20produced%20annually%2C%20faces%20the%20challenge%20of%2030-35%25%20of%20it%20going%20to%20waste%2C%E2%80%9D%20Mistry%20says%2C%20explaining%20why%20he%20chose%20the%20fruit.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20waste%2C%20primarily%20in%20the%20form%20of%20skin%20and%20seeds%2C%20provides%20a%20sustainable%20raw%20material%20for%20Bioleather%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20Mistry%20says%20that%20tomatoes%20are%20rich%20in%20pectin%2C%20a%20natural%20polymer%20that%20enhances%20flexibility%20and%20strength.%20Their%20fibrous%20structure%20and%20natural%20oils%20help%20create%20a%20leather-like%20texture%20while%20ensuring%20biodegradability.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FWhat-Was-14-1_11zon-1738158551-1755515878.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tomato%20waste%20is%20transformed%20into%20Bioleather%20by%20The%20Bio%20Company%2C%20now%20used%20in%20fashion%2C%20bags%2C%20and%20footwear.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FWhat-Was-14-1_11zon-1738158551-1755515878.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FWhat-Was-14-1_11zon-1738158551-1755515878-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FWhat-Was-14-1_11zon-1738158551-1755515878-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FWhat-Was-14-1_11zon-1738158551-1755515878-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FWhat-Was-14-1_11zon-1738158551-1755515878-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%